{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Bonfire"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 12], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [44, 112], "text": [" Creates a bonfire simulation using the sparse pyro solver. "]}, {"body": [{"body": [], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "attrs": {"src": "/videos/shelf_bonfire.mp4"}, "extent": [112, 120], "container": true, "type": "video"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "video_group"}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [184, 243], "text": ["This tool sets up a sparse pyro simulation of a bonfire."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [169, 184], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [271, 351], "text": ["The shelf tool creates a node network consisting of the following components."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [674, 923], "text": ["The density is further modified by the ", {"text": ["Attribute Noise SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes//sop/attribnoise", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes//sop/attribnoise"}, " to provide variation in the source. The ", {"text": ["Attribute Adjust Vector SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes//sop/attribadjustvector", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes//sop/attribadjustvector"}, " is used to animate the velocity source at the base over time."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"text": ["bonfire/bofire_base"], "type": "code"}, " chain is responsible for setting up the density and velocity sources. The start of this chain controls the shape of the fire\u2019s base. You can switch out this node for another geometry object if you want to change the look of the base. For example, you could use geometry representing fire logs."], "extent": [351, 674], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1253, 1301], "text": ["Boost the ", {"text": ["Buoyancy Scale"], "type": "ui"}, ". "]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1301, 1366], "text": ["This will also increase the height of the fire."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Increase the speed of the flames"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_buoyancy"}, "extent": [1171, 1215], "container": true, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1438, 1607], "text": ["Adjust the ", {"text": ["Disturbance"], "type": "ui"}, ", ", {"text": ["Shredding"], "type": "ui"}, ", and ", {"text": ["Turbulence"], "type": "ui"}, " parameters on the ", {"text": ["Shape"], "type": "ui"}, " tab of the ", {"text": ["Sparse Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes//dop/pyrosolver_sparse", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes//dop/pyrosolver_sparse"}, ". "]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1607, 1769], "text": ["Disturbance generically breaks up the flames, shredding redirects the velocities (creating the\n        licks), and ", {"text": ["Turbulence"], "type": "ui"}, " mimics a chaotic wind."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Change the motion of fire"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_shape"}, "extent": [1366, 1403], "container": true, "type": "task"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "task_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": ["bonfire_simulation"], "type": "code"}, " contains the dynamics network that consumes the sources and carries out the simulation. The parameters on the ", {"text": ["Sparse Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes//dop/pyrosolver_sparse", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes//dop/pyrosolver_sparse"}, " have the greatest influence on the speed and height of the fire."], "extent": [923, 1171], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [3746, 3828], "text": ["Change the menu next to ", {"text": ["Smoke Color"], "type": "ui"}, " from ", {"text": ["Constant"], "type": "ui"}, " to ", {"text": ["Use Ramp"], "type": "ui"}, ". "]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [3828, 3929], "text": ["Set the ", {"text": ["Density Range"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter to control the color of the smoke at given density values."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [3929, 4026], "text": ["Set the ", {"text": ["Smoke Color Ramp"], "type": "ui"}, " to change the color of the smoke based on ", {"text": ["Density Range"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": [" Change the color of the smoke based on density"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "tip1"}, "extent": [3676, 3732], "container": true, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [4125, 4282], "text": ["Change the ", {"text": ["Absorption Color"], "type": "ui"}, ". The value of ", {"text": ["0.425"], "type": "code"}, " (red),", {"text": ["0.36"], "type": "code"}, "(green), ", {"text": ["0.3"], "type": "code"}, "(blue) could be a good starting point for more realistic looking smoke."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [" Change the color of the smoke based on how light scatters through the volume"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "tip2"}, "extent": [4026, 4111], "container": true, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "ord", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4346, 4398], "text": ["Turn on the ", {"text": ["Use Control Volume"], "type": "ui"}, " checkbox. "]}, {"type": "ord", "blevel": 6, "indent": 4, "extent": [4398, 4586], "text": ["Set ", {"text": ["Density Control Volume"], "type": "ui"}, " on the ", {"text": ["Bindings"], "type": "ui"}, " tabs to the field that you want to use to affect the density. Usually ", {"text": ["temperature"], "type": "code"}, " or ", {"text": ["flame"], "type": "code"}, " are good choices for this purpose."]}], "type": "ord_group", "container": true}], "indent": 0, "text": [" Scale smoke density using an other volume"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "tip3"}, "extent": [4282, 4332], "container": true, "type": "task"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "task_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"text": ["bonfire/object_merge"], "type": "code"}, " chain extracts the results of the simulation back into a SOP geometry. A ", {"text": ["Pyro Bake Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume"}, " node sets the proper viewport visualization settings and creates a matching render material. If you dive inside this node, you modify some of the parameters on the ", {"text": ["Pyro Shader"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/pyroadvancedshader", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/pyroadvancedshader"}, " to do the following."], "extent": [1769, 2142], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord"}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [5080, 5277], "text": ["For more accurate color display, use the Academy Color Encoding System (ACES). See ", {"fragment": "#aces", "text": ["Shading and rendering"], "value": "/pyro/shading#aces", "fullpath": "/pyro/shading#aces", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " in the Pyro chapter for information on how to set this up."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [5277, 5444], "text": ["Add a ", {"text": ["Spot Light"], "fullpath": "/render/lights", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/render/lights"}, " for better visualization in the viewport and an ", {"text": ["Environment Light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/envlight", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/obj/envlight"}, " with custom hdri map for rendering."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [5444, 5661], "text": ["Add a small amount of sharpening on the density field to bring out a bit more detail, using the ", {"text": ["Sharpen Volume"], "type": "ui"}, " option in the ", {"text": ["Pyro Bake Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume"}, "'s ", {"text": ["Quick Setups"], "type": "ui"}, " dropdown menu."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 7, "type": "bullet", "extent": [5661, 5840], "text": ["Choose the ", {"text": ["Create Lights/Cameras"], "type": "ui"}, " option from the Pyro Bake Volume\u2019s  ", {"text": ["Quick Setups"], "type": "ui"}, " dropdown menu to quickly setup the volume for rendering with lights and cameras."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Tips"], "attrs": {"id": "common_spyro_tip"}, "extent": [5038, 5049], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Understanding Bonfire"], "extent": [243, 271], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "title": ["Bonfire"], "summary": [" Creates a bonfire simulation using the sparse pyro solver. "], "attrs": {"tags": "pyro", "icon": "SHELF/fire"}, "included": ["/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume", "/nodes/vop/pyroadvancedshader", "/shelf/spyro_fireball"], "type": "root"}